dev_team.name: Mitch Hall
dev_team.write_up: I finished the 201 class thinking I had a pretty good idea of how software development would go. Then I started the first week of 301 and learned that didn't have a good idea at all. However what we have learned in 301, and the why things are done a certain, way makes sense. It certainly allowed us to work together effectively during this group assignment.

dev_team.name: Trevor Dobson
dev_team.write_up: Trevor is a veteran of the United States Army. Originally from Iowa, he is now settled in Washington for the foreseeable future. He hopes to combine Code Fellows with his background in business management to jump-start a career in the tech industry. During his free time he enjoys hiking, golfing, and traveling.

dev_team.name: Tiger Hsu
dev_team.write_up: He is a veteran of the coast guard and is currently a reservist in the Air Force.He enjoys learning coding and hopes one day he will be able to be a game developer.On his free time he enjoys woodworking and working on cars.
